## Brand assets (separate license · planning-003 §A.5.8)

The brand assets at `brand/` — including but not limited to the bracketed
"i" mark, `Ivaronix.html`, `tokens.css`, `tokens.json`, the wordmark in
all weights, the favicon set, the OG image templates, and any future
logo variant — are NOT covered by the MIT grant above.

These assets are reserved trademarks of the Ivaronix project. They may
be used only under nominative-fair-use rules:

  - Citing or reviewing Ivaronix (e.g. blog posts, talks, comparative
    benchmarks) — permitted, with attribution and without implying
    endorsement.
  - Building software ON TOP OF Ivaronix's open-source code — permitted;
    use a different mark for your distribution.
  - Forking the codebase to ship a competing product at a confusable
    domain (`ivaronix-x.app`, `ivaronix.studio`, `myivaronix.app` etc.)
    with the brand assets attached — NOT permitted.
  - Embedding the receipt-verifier widget on your site — permitted,
    with the existing widget chrome.

In short: the code is yours under MIT. The brand is the project's.
See `BRAND.md` at repo root for the operative rule.
